opn_sm_bz <- read.csv("open small businesses.csv", fileEncoding = "UTF-8-BOM")

opn_sm_bz$State.Names <- as.factor(opn_sm_bz$State.Names)
opn_sm_bz$Month <- as.factor(opn_sm_bz$Month)
opn_sm_bz$Industries <- as.factor(opn_sm_bz$Industries)
opn_sm_bz$Neighborhood_Classes <- as.factor(opn_sm_bz$Neighborhood_Classes)
opn_sm_bz$Neighborhood_Classes <- factor(opn_sm_bz$Neighborhood_Classes,
                                         levels = c("High Income", "Middle Income", "Low Income"))

Plots

Covid Case Rates by State Text

viz <- ggplot(covid, aes(Month, new_case_rate, color = case_rate)) + 
  geom_text(alpha = 0.8, size = 3, aes(label = State.Names)) +
  theme_bw() + theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) + 
  labs(title = "New Case Rates by State", x = "month", y = "new case rate") +
  scale_color_gradient(name = "case rate", low = "#56B1F7", high = "#132B43") +
  scale_y_continuous(sec.axis = dup_axis(name = NULL))
viz

Change in Revenue by Change in Spending

viz <- ggplot(rev_spend, aes(spend_all, revenue_all, color = month)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.7) + 
  stat_smooth(method = "lm", color = "#113789") + theme(strip.background =element_rect(fill="#949494"))+
  theme_bw() + theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) + 
  labs(title = "Change in Revenue by Change in Spending", x = "change in spending", y = "change in revenue") +
  scale_color_discrete(name = "month") +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(scale = 100, accuracy = 1L),
                     limits = c(-0.75, 0.15)) +
  scale_x_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(scale = 100, accuracy = 1L),
                     limits = c(-0.40, .05))
viz
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'
## Warning: Removed 5 rows containing non-finite values (stat_smooth).
## Warning: Removed 5 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

Monthly Trend for Revenue Change vs. Spending Habits

viz <- ggplot(rev_spend, aes(spend_all, revenue_all, fill = month)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.7) + 
  stat_smooth(method = "lm", color = "#113789") + theme(strip.background =element_rect(fill="#949494"))+
  theme_bw() + theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) + 
  labs(title = "Monthly Trend for Change in Revenue by Spending", x = "change in spending", y = "change in revenue") +
  scale_fill_discrete(name = "month") +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(scale = 100, accuracy = 1L), sec.axis = dup_axis(name = NULL)) +
  scale_x_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(scale = 100, accuracy = 1L), sec.axis = dup_axis(name = NULL))
viz
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

Change in Open Businesses by Revenue

viz <- ggplot(rev_spend, aes(revenue_all, merchants_all, color = month)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.7) + 
  stat_smooth(method = "lm", color = "#113789") + theme(strip.background =element_rect(fill="#949494"))+

  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(scale = 100, accuracy = 1L),
                     limits = c(-0.5, 0.10)) +
